<P align="center"><strong>(updated 
  August 7, 2013)</strong></P>

<P><br>
  + Florida first held a sales tax holiday for school supplies in 2007. This was not re-enacted in 2008-09. Massachusetts first held a sales tax holiday in 2004. It was not re-enacted in 2008.<br>
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Georgia first held a school supply holiday in 2004 and energy efficiency holiday in 2006. They were not re-enacted in 2010-11.<br>
  * Details for some state programs are not available yet, website points to 2011 program.<br>
  
  Note, if your state is not listed, legislation has not been approved authorizing a sales tax holiday. Contact your state legislator for more information.<br>
If you have any corrections, please direct your inquiry to <a href="../sendmail.php?F_name=ron" target="_blank">Ronald Alt</a>.</P>
